  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a neural-network surrogate model used to predict hemolysis index for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A single training run was performed and point-estimate validation metrics are reported; no characterization of seed-to-seed prediction variance is included.",
